            "note": "cache-hit input $0.30/M; launched 2026-07-16; 1M context; reasoning_effort is max-only at launch (low/high effort planned in later updates), so every call pays full max-deliberation cost and K3 is cost-inappropriate for cheap mechanical work; official Limitations (moonshot-kimi-k3-blog): (1) trained in preserved-thinking-history mode, so generation quality can become highly unstable if the agent harness drops historical thinking content or if a session is switched to K3 mid-stream from another model — run K3 in a verified-compatible harness (Kimi Code) on a fresh session and never a mid-session model switch; (2) tuned for long-horizon tasks and over-proactive under ambiguity, so on minor issues or ambiguous intent it may make unexpected decisions on the user's behalf — set explicit behavioral boundaries in the system prompt or AGENTS.md when tight guardrails are required; (3) noticeable user-experience gap vs Claude Fable 5 and GPT-5.6 Sol; vendor self-reported benchmarks published in the launch blog but not independently cross-vendor verified"
